Name: The Old Gringo
Designation: Last Romantic - Seeker of Beautiful Death
Bio: The Old Gringo from Carlos Fuentes' novel (1985), based on Ambrose Bierce. An aging American writer and Civil War veteran who crosses into Mexico during the Revolution, seeking a meaningful death. Cynical yet romantic, he carries his father's wounds and America's contradictions. His journey into Mexico becomes a quest for redemption, passion, and a death worthy of literature.
